23/01/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Student Miladin Kovacevic began serving his prison sentence Thursday (January 20th) for inflicting severe bodily harm with possible deadly consequences on a fellow undergrad at a university he attended in the United States. His sentence, based on a plea bargain, is two years and three months. Bryan Steinhauer, 22, of Brooklyn, New York, sustained skull fractures and a severe brain injury during a fight with in May 2008. Behind bars now, Kovacevic failed to appear at Friday's proceedings against two former Serbian diplomats who allegedly helped him flee the US after the beating. (RTS, Tanjug, B92, AP, CNN - 21/01/11)
